	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				How to reword it? I'd suggest splitting the questions into two or three rather than one generic one.  I said that I didn't like it (and have no plans on going back), but without knowing what part I'm talking about unfairly lumps that sentiment to the whole product.  My main anger is in two things.<BR>
<BR>
a)  creating yet another wiz spires where you get attacked with regularity when you port in.  I've shown up half dead, just because of sometimes zoning slow, and yet the creatures on the other end can start wacking on me before I'm even given control on my end.  This stinks.  Give the frequent and repeatable problems with zoning (I'm a 44wiz and as the night goes on, zoning gets slower and slower til I eventually get kicked out of the game (get booted out of game and have to reenter either the game or reselect which character I want to play)).  So, it's bad enough that there is apparently creeping crud in your memory management, but then to purposely put a wizard port site which is dangerous stinks.<BR>
<BR>
b)  The game is challenging enough without being aggroed all over the place.  Since verant CHOSE to have variable duration invis spells (another one of my pet peeves, other nice spells are not variable duration (SOW, Clarity, etc.)), then traveling through Velious is problematic, AND, detracts from the fun of the expansion.  <BR>
<BR>
Now - this has all been stated in other comments that were stated in the appropriate forum - not here.  My point for putting it here is though, if I liked the graphics, and liked the UI, and appreciate some of the plots you've added (I have heard about but not experienced first hand), then how do I answer that survey?  I chose to say &quot;not satisfied&quot; or whatever it's called, because the negatives I've listed outweight the positives and I'll stay in Kunark for awhile, or at least until the playability issues are addressed.  Verant needs to realize that not everyone is a member of a huge powerful guild and therefore has to sometimes (quite often) travel solo to get to where they are trying to find a group.  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
